column5: Hi,  I have been a long time lurker,  thought I would finally intruduce myself.  I do most of my fishing in the Muskoka area and mainly fish for bass.  I look forward to contributing to the board in the future.  I have attached a link below of a video I created from a fishing weekend I go to every year with some guys at work.  Its pretty cool.    http://my.break.com/content/view.aspx?ContentID=496339
Dude catches second fish without even putting the first one down. Thats was a great vid welcome to the site lob fisher
Welcome aboard.  Cool video.  I've had that happen too but the second fish didn't cooperate enough to actually hook himself.  Just attacked the lure floating on the water.

Real cool video.  I see Musky fisherman use screen names like "MuskyBob" or "Musky Fisher" .. same goes with bass/pike/etc... soo... you fish for lobsters? want to share some tips and recipes?  Welcome aboard. It's a great place
lob is the Acronym for the lake I predominantly fish.
Awesome video and welcome aboard as well.
Uh i see, i was just fooling around haha.
